rComments: This prof was very quick to respond to questions and is very accessible. Would recommend him for sure. I took this course during the summer and was super compacted. This made it very difficult to absorb the information in time for the quizzes which were every week. On a side note, the labs were the worst part (led by another prof).

Biochemistry is generally a difficult topic but Dr. Horsman wants you to get the highest grade possible. Instead of large midterms we had multiple quizzes that were collectively worth 30% of the final grade. His exams are MCQ and the lectures are necessary to pass because the powerpoint alone doesn't provide all the info.
